Report the outlier durations for the surveys

assessmentDurationOutliers.Rd

This function report the outlier durations for the surveys

assessmentDurationOutliers(
  ds = NULL,
  dates = NULL,
  sdval = NULL,
  reportingcol = NULL
)

Arguments

ds

dataset as a data.frame object
dates

fields as a list of string where the survey start and end date is stored (c('start_date','end_date'))
sdval

number of standard deviation for which the duration within is considered as acceptable
reportingcol

columns as a list of string name from the dataset you want in the result (c('col1','col2',...))

Value

ret_log the report

Examples

{
ds <- HighFrequencyChecks::sample_dataset
dates <- c("survey_start","end_survey")
sdval <- 5
reportingcol <- c("enumerator_id","X_uuid")

list[dst,ret_log,var,graph] <- assessmentDurationOutliers(ds,
                                                          dates,
                                                          sdval,
                                                          reportingcol)
head(ret_log,10)
}
#>     enumerator_id                               X_uuid duration    Zscore
#> 148            18 25291b40-5a3b-486c-ad4f-52e38939234f      192  5.357483
#> 198         10021 a05f7999-53c4-4ab6-a243-2a1a86edde6c      340 10.436367
